You picked it up so quickly.

297
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:27,720
It's because

298
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:28,680
I had a helper.

299
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:32,280
Miss.

300
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:32,960
You are tired.

301
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:34,490
I'll go pour you a cup of tea.

302
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:41,720
Good job.

303
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:44,120
Oh, right.

304
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:46,360
Just now, when I was looking through the ledgers,

305
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:47,440
I found something.

306
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,560
From the purchase orders of those British merchants,

307
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,960
it can be seen that for the past few months,

308
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:54,760
they have been continuously driving down prices.

309
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,480
Just as I thought.

310
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:02,040
Miss!

311
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:02,920
Miss!

312
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,440
Bad news!

313
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:06,520
The British merchants are causing trouble in our tea garden!

314
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,240
Let's go.

315
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:07,900
Take a look.

316
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:21,160
I told you.

317
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,520
If you don't pay enough today,

318
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:24,720
don't even think about taking this tea.

319
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,880
I have already paid.

320
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:27,800
Back off.

321
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,800
You are so shameless.

322
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:40,480
I'll teach you some manners today.

323
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:44,000
Get lost.

324
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:44,560
Attack.

325
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:45,680
Stop!

326
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:46,800
What are you doing?

327
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,280
Miss is here.

328
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,690
Miss, you're finally here.

329
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:52,770
Are you alright?

330
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,120
We're fine.

331
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:55,560
Who are you?

332
00:14:57,560 --> 00:15:00,160
This is the new head of the Hu family,

333
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:01,600
Miss Hu Linglong.

334
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,840
What exactly is going on here?

335
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,960
Miss.

336
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:09,640
You don't know.

337
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,520
It's this Brit.

338
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:12,560
For the past few months,

339
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:14,960
he's been forcing the prices down at the tea garden.

340
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:17,080
Today he even wanted to use a few coppers

341
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,960
to buy our tea.

342
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,840
He's leaving us no way to survive.

343
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:21,520
Yes.

344
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:23,200
They are leaving us no way to survive.

345
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,960
This is too much.

346
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:28,800
It's them.

347
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:33,360
I am Charles.

348
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,280
Miss Hu.

349
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,640
You know the rules.

350
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:37,840
You are not like them.

351
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:45,360
Hu Linglong.

352
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:45,840
Watch out.
